              <li>In landslide-prone areas, be aware of steep slopes, maintain proper drainage, and look for new cracks in the ground. Landslides can occur repeatedly in the same places.</li>
              <li>Stay alert to unusual sounds like cracking trees, rocks, or walls, especially during prolonged or heavy rainfall.</li>
              <li>Move away from windows and areas where landslide debris might enter your residence.</li>
              <li>Stay calm and evacuate the affected structure when safe to do so and call 911.</li>
              <li>Any work done to stabilize a slope should be done by a professionally licensed engineer or geologist.</li>
            </ul>
